        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article I     </h2>   
                <h3> Incorporation </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    The name of this organization shall be “Charleston Area Justice Ministry (CAJM)”.
                </li>
                <li>
                    CAJM shall be a non-profit corporation, established in accordance with section 501 (c)(3) of the Tax Code of the Internal Revenue Service and the laws of the State of South Carolina.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Authority is vested in the Annual Assembly (“Annual Assembly”), which is the ultimate decision-making body for the organization which delegates authority and responsibility between meetings to the Leadership Senate.
                </li>               
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article II </h2>   
                <h3> Affiliation with Direct Action and Research Training Center, Inc. (DART) </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    CAJM shall maintain an affiliation with the Direct Action and Research Training Center, Inc. (DART). 
                </li>
                <li>
                    CAJM shall rely on DART to provide training and consulting support for CAISC leaders and to recruit and train new organizing staff.  
                </li>           
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article III </h2>   
                <h3> Membership  </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>          
                <li> 
                    CAJM shall be an organization of congregations or community organizations.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Congregations become member organizations of CAJM after subscribing to the following covenant: _______ (name of the congregation), enters into a covenant with CAJM for the purpose of more successfully practicing our values in our community by:
                    <ol>
                        <li> Building a Justice Ministry Network in our congregation; </li>  
                        <li> Engaging in a listening process, training leaders, developing solutions, and taking action to improve community conditions;  </li> 
                        <li> Accepting responsibility for the financial health of the organization by contributing annually and by supporting CAJM fundraising efforts; </li>
                        <li> Voicing the concerns of the members of our congregations during Assemblies and fully supporting the agreed upon goals; and finally... </li>
                        <li> Selecting leaders (Justice Ministry Team members) from our congregation to attend all CAJM Leadership Senate meetings. </li>
                    </ol>
                </li> 
                <li>
                    Voting rights of member congregations at the Annual Assembly, Leadership Senate and Justice Ministry Team Assemblies shall depend upon the payment of dues in a timely manner.
                </li>     
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article IV </h2>   
                <h3> Membership  </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li> All powers derive from and ultimate authority is invested in the Annual Assembly including the authority to: 
                    <ol>
                        <li> Adopt policies, set issue priorities,  and authorize formation of issue/action committees; </li>
                        <li> Elect the officers and Nominating Committee of CAJM; </li>
                        <li> Amend this constitution in accordance with Article XII; and, </li>
                        <li> Act on any other business of the organization properly brought before it. </li>
                    </ol>
                </li>  
                <li> The Annual Assembly shall meet at least once a year on a date selected by the CAJM Leadership Senate.  Meetings of the Annual Assembly may be called at any time by the Leadership Senate.  Three-week’s written notice shall be given of any called meeting.</li>
                <li> Each member congregation shall send delegates to the Annual Meeting. Each member congregation shall be expected to send delegations composed of Justice Ministry Team and Justice Ministry Network Members. 
                    <ol>
                        <li> Only delegates who are present at the Annual Meeting shall have the right to vote. Each delegate present shall be entitled to one vote. A delegate shall represent only one organization. </li>
                        <li> The Annual Assembly, excepting those delegations involved in any dispute regarding seat, voice or vote, shall, by a simple majority of voting members present, be the final judge in determining the seating of delegates and alternates. </li>
                    </ol>
                </li> 
                <li> Notice of any Annual Meeting, including the agenda, shall be published to all member congregations at least two weeks prior to the meeting. </li> 
                <li> The delegates present at any properly convened Annual Assembly shall constitute a quorum provided that at least one-half (1/2) of the member congregations have a delegate present. </li> 
                <li> The Co-Presidents shall call the Annual Assembly to order and preside over the Assembly. </li>
            </ol>
        </div>        

